content:
@Dunham I'm not seeing how Mirhawk is scummy.<br>
<br>
I AM, however, seeing how Disturbed is scummy.

There's no Vig, there was only one NK.<br>
<br>
@Ice &amp; Bacde - Why are you two talking about Vigging?

@absta, a lot of times vigilantes only get one shot, so they don't use it their first night. Also, unless you're reasonably confident about taking your shot, it's risky to shoot night 1 as you're statistically more likely to hit town than scum. I don't believe I've ever drawn a vig role PM, but if I did I probably wouldn't shoot night 1. Especially if I only had 1 shot.<br>
<br>
Also Bacde, the only reason I'm saying it will be pro-town for a vig to shoot you <div style="display:inline;font-style:italic">even if you're town</div> is because we're going to HAVE to lynch you anyway. Night killing a town player &gt; mislynching a town player. This is all rendered moot because I'm pretty sure you're scum.

I will admit that jmo's last post looks emotional and charged and potentially scummy, but I can relate to reacting that way when I previously believed pressure on me to be unfounded in other games.  I'm still not seeing him as scum, just frustrated.<br>
<br>
@jmo, who do you think is scum?  Why?

Iam is a gut scum read. But gut isn't worth talking about. <br>
<br>
@Ice - Who'd you protect N1?
